PLACEHOLDER_FAQ_TITLE: Frequently Asked Questions about Sui Transaction Analysis
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: Sui transaction analysis allows you to monitor and gain insights into new transactions happening on the Sui blockchain in real-time. This can help you detect new token transfers, contract deployments, and other on-chain activity as it occurs.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_2: How does the Sui transaction analysis app work?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: Our app connects directly to Sui nodes and listens for new blocks being added to the chain. When a new block is detected, we parse all the transactions inside and extract relevant data like sender, recipient, amount transferred, contract data, etc. This data is then processed and presented through an intuitive interface.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_3: What kind of data can I see with this app?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: You can view detailed information on token transfers, smart contract deployments and executions, new accounts created, and any other types of transactions occurring on Sui. Charts and graphs provide visualizations of key metrics like transaction volumes over time.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_4: Can I get alerts for certain transaction types?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: Yes, you can set up customized alerts to notify you whenever specific transaction criteria are met, such as large token transfers above a certain amount or activity from a particular Sui address you're monitoring.

FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Yes, the app only interacts with the public Sui blockchain. Your private keys and personal data are never accessed or stored.
